Enforces that retired identifiers (deprecated via ADR) never appear in live code or documentation — only in the decision ledger (docs/DECISIONS.md), retired archives (docs/retired/**), audit docs, and generated context (which gets regenerated). Uses `git ls-files` to enumerate tracked and untracked-not-ignored files, excluding `.context/` since it's regenerated.

The `BANNED` array lists retired terms to reject: `ctx-access`, `init-task`, `end-task`, `served_nodes`, `SPEC.md`, `CTX_AGENT_MODEL`. When an ADR retires a concept, its grep pattern is added here.

`is_allowed()` whitelists paths where retired terms are permitted to survive: decision history, retired design docs, audit docs, and this script itself (template/ variant included). All other files are checked.

Emits diagnostics as `FAIL: path:line:content -- retired identifier, see docs/DECISIONS.md for the ADR that retired it…` — the `path:line:` prefix must come first because ctx-verify's `split_loc` parser looks for it there; any text after the line number is safe and carries the guidance message. Uses `/dev/null` forced to the grep arguments to guarantee the multi-file `file:line:` prefix even when one file is checked, and `|| true` to prevent grep's exit code from terminating the loop early.